Its possible to like &quot;the game&quot; and not like some aspects of the class you play or &quot;the game&quot;.  And more so it is quite possible to like EQ and just not enjoy having to be rediculed by folks like yourself.<br>
<br>
My feeling is that there are countless people that have a mage character (in addition to others) that simply don't point out issues because they are afraid of being &quot;labeled&quot;.<br>
<br>
Many of you that are vocal enough to post see things from the rose colored glasses of guilds that can support classes that have no major impact on the high end game.  Others here have already given up on the mage class and have moved on to other classes to play.<br>
<br>
Overall I don't expect to see any massive improvments to Mages.  Part of this is because the communtiy does not exist and just does not care anymore.<br>
<br>
