<br>
1.  First of all, I was not complaining about gear period.  If you read my posts at all, you would see that I still wear a green silk drape and am quite happy with it.  I assume you may have been addressing fq2010, but I am not sure.<br>
<br>
2.  Point of fact, I did help in starting a guild on Mith Marr, and we are growing.  However, our main purpose is to have friends, not raid all the time.  Like I also said earlier, guild choice is a matter of preference.  I like my guild and the people in it.  None of us have time to go on weekend long raids, but we have events, socialize, and generally have a lot of fun playing EQ.<br>
<br>
3.  I guess there are two ways to look at the game.  On the one hand you have those who like interaction, semi-role playing (EQ will never be on par with real RPGs), and enjoy a casual form of entertainment.  On the other hand, you have those who see acquisition of gear as the main objective, which requires raiding and, as you put it, being forced to cooperate.  I like to think I have never been forced to cooperate in the game.  I like working with people.  I like soloing too.<br>
<br>
Laugh if you want, but my &quot;golden ring&quot; is going to be the Arch Mage's robe from Thurgadin.  That is the item I hope to get.  If along the way my guild grows enough to do raids and try epics, so be it.  I may even attend a raid or two just to see the planes, but that is not my main goal.<br>
<br>
4.  What do you think about twinking, just plain old twinking? Everyone seems to skirt this issue.<br>
<br>
5.  I said in an earlier post that age does not matter other than in terms of playing time.  Well, playing time certainly is important.  Most people, not saying all, who work full-time and have other priorities can not dedicate 8 hours a day or entire weekends to the game, so even though I like the get-up-and-go attitude of your idea about starting a guild and going for it, I seriously doubt fq2010 has that kind of time to devote to the game.  Out of curiosity did you start/help start your guild?<br>
<br>
6.  Let me point this out one more time for those of you who still do not get it.  You are quick to jump on casual players, telling them to leave if they don't like EQ in its current state.  Well, like I said, if the casual gamers should all decide to leave, do you think EQ would survive?  Only with huge turnover in numbers of casual gamers.  EQ has over 380,000 subscribers.  Do you honestly think the majority of those are in the high end, raiding aspect of the game?<br>
<br>
7.  You want people to quit complaining, and I agree.  However, notice that much of the complaining revolves around Call of the Hero, the epic quest, no pets on raids, and spells resists on raids.  Complaining is not limited to those not in large guilds.  Sadly, it is part of human nature.<br>
<br>
I just wanted to add these thoughts.  Also, it would be nice if we all address who we are responding to in our posts.  I know we all sometimes forget to do so, but it helps to avoid confusion.<br>
<br>
Copperrfield<br>
