<br>
I think I acknowledged that of course those who play more will have opportunities to go further in the game.  That is only logical, but what I take issue with is telling people that don't like the idea, don't have the time, or even just don't want to play as often as some people do to leave.  If those who are casual gamers can acknowledge that &quot;hard core&quot; gamers will go further in the game, perhaps those hard core gamers could also acknowledge that they need the casual players financial support to keep EQ going.  <br>
<br>
If you really think Verant doesn't need/want the money of casual gamers, you are sadly mistaken.  Why do you think there are 50 or so levels of the game that can be completed without huge raids?  If Verant wanted the game to be strictly about what happens in the high end, i.e. huge raids, characters would start with the power of a level 60 and get even stronger.  Raids now would be the tip of the iceberg.<br>
<br>
To Thon,<br>
<br>
First, I have nothing against twinking.  How each person plays is his/her business, but I do see many people in the game that seem to get their characters confused.  No doubt one of your characters bought/earned the equipment your warrior wears, but your Ogre did not earn it.  All I have been trying to get across is that, logically, a character buying planar gear would be no different than a level 1 having equipment he/she would have to be level 40 to get normally.  <br>
<br>
Maybe looking at it another way would help.  Say you are 16 and your parents get you a car.  Now they could get you the green silk drape of cars, a Ford, or they could go all out and get you that nice Apothic BMW you have been dreaming of.  Either way you end up with a car you did not earn or could not get on your own.  <br>
<br>
Notice I am agreeing with you that buying planar gear would not be earning it per se <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uknorotpumaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knorot Pumaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of The Elements</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/01 6:01:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The Luclin Uber Magician Robe!</span><hr size=1> I see you are agreeing but that Green Silken Drape/SMR/BC Robe can be gotten by the casual gamer and a group of 5 of their friends that don't play as much, where as that Apothic Robe can be gotten by the people who play more and do large raids.  I know some servers do *shudder* public raids, so there is always a chance that a casual gamer can get the better gear.  No drop will always be no drop, it is a good idea.<br>
