<br>
Casual gamers know that they play 2 hours tops a night, that might be a bit high *shrug*, and they get with their group of friends and kill stuff, in Butcherblock or Seb or someplace.  The power gamers play 6+ hours at a time, and are able to organize large raids and get numerous people to a location in usually minutes.  These raids usually last longer than what a casual gamer can give, but for the high end game, there is still places like HS, Seb, SG, or DN that you can fight in with 1 group and do stuff in the amount of time a casual gamer can give to EQ.<br>
